{"type":"message","id":"fe1dc300","parentId":"b5d3fc87","timestamp":"2026-03-09T16:22:17.119Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_27074e31bff5417d8c0023a7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-08\n\n- Installed ClawHub skill `scrapling-official` into `openclaw-workspace/skills/scrapling-official` via the `clawhub-install` skill.\n- Reviewed `scrapling-official/SKILL.md` and summarized setup + usage: requires Python 3.10+, `pip install \"scrapling[all]>=0.4.1\"`, then `scrapling install --force`; recommended command order is `extract get` → `fetch` → `stealthy-fetch`.\n- Confirmed `python3` path with `which python3`: `/Users/liuyuan/miniforge3/bin/python3`.\n- Checked `${OPENCLAW_DATA_DIR}/context-engineering`; task artifacts appear complete, including final blog files (`context-engineering-blog-zh.md`, `context-engineering-blog-zh-third-person.md`, `context-engineering-blog-final-20260307.md`, `.humanized.md`) plus notes and source dumps.\n- Looked up the film 《我们的样子像极了爱情》 and confirmed it is currently available on iQIYI; extracted an iQIYI jump link from search results.\n- Diagnosed macOS screenshot permission chain for this session: commands run under `/bin/zsh` launched by `openclaw-gateway`, parent `openclaw`; underlying executable for both `openclaw` and `openclaw-gateway` is `/Users/liuyuan/.nvm/versions/node/v24.13.0/bin/node`.\n- After user granted permissions, captured a desktop screenshot successfully to `${OPENCLAW_DATA_DIR}/screenshots/desktop-20260308-174343.png`.\n- To send the screenshot over Telegram, copied it into the workspace as `/Users/liuyuan/workspace/openclaw-workspace/desktop-20260308-174343.png` because direct send from `openclaw-data` was blocked by allowed-directory restrictions; then sent it successfully.\n- Investigated OpenClaw builtin memory session indexing and found a bug: `shouldSyncSessions()` skipped sessions for `reason === \"session-start\" || reason === \"watch\"` before checking `needsFullReindex`, which could let full reindexes rebuild memory files while dropping session transcript indexing.\n- Patched OpenClaw source in a fresh clone at `${OPENCLAW_DATA_DIR}/src/openclaw`, added regression test `src/memory/manager.session-reindex.test.ts`, verified tests pass, and opened upstream PR: `openclaw/openclaw#39732` (`fix(memory): preserve session indexing during full reindex`).\n- Applied the same patch locally to the installed OpenClaw dist on this Mac and verified `openclaw memory index --agent main --force` now preserves session indexing (`sessions = 5 files / 172 chunks`).\n- Removed `agents.defaults.memorySearch.extraPaths` from `openclaw.json` to stop indexing the bundled OpenClaw docs, then rebuilt memory. Result: `main` now indexes only `memory + sessions` (`21 memory files / 100 chunks`, `5 session files / 172 chunks`, total `26 files / 272 chunks`).\n- Verified by direct SQLite queries that session chunks now contain expected conversation keywords such as `openclaw-gateway`, `爱奇艺`, and `scrapling-official`. Practical conclusion: session transcripts are now stably indexed; when search still surfaces `memory/*.md` first, that is mainly a ranking/summary-density effect rather than missing session data.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773073337118}}
